The paper deals with image classification and uses an adversarial autoencoder to learn the latent feature space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a decision tree classifier and focuses on explaining black box models, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with visualizing images, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
